column18: Please share any other suggestions or ideas that would help us enhance your experience at Gesa Power House Theatre. If you would like someone to respond to your feedback, please include your contact information. Thank you!

column17: It was wonderful! Vibrant! Fun!
Excellent
Excellent show! Loved it!
The concert was excellent. Great sound, comfortable seating, reasonable price. We love attending concerts at the GESA Power House Theatre.
So wonderful! Please bring them back again - we were able to go to this concert and the one 5 years ago - would see them every year if they would come!

A very entertaining show.  I am not a fan of Celtic music but my spouse is.  I  found the group engaging and talented.  They had the whole theatre participating in their program.  The sound/light tech was professional and on the mark for the performance.
Fabulous
Incredible

Great!

column18: When we booked there were few seats left. Making some kind of effort to sell our seats to someone else and providing a refund would have been appreciated after we notified you we could not come.

column17: Too loud.  I left at intermission.
Very good quality all around.
column18: Loved this show!  Really like the very talented non-mainstream music you book.

column17: This group is fantastic! HOWEVER… we left at the intermission as it was overwhelmingly LOUD! Gesa is a small theater , and performers should adjust the volume of their performance . At times it was almost painful. It was also difficult to understand some of the dialogue d/t accents. Understand that is my problem but I did miss much of the discussions and funny stories! We came home and watched the group on  uTube where we could turn the volume down!
It was a fun evening. I think that everything was working correctly and that the audience had a great time.
Heard music loud and clear but missed most of the interaction with audience because they spoke very softly. Missed most of their jokes
Professional!
column18: We loved the band and had the best time. Definitely worth the trip from the Tri- Cities

column17:
We loved the intimate venue. We sat in the balcony and a couple thoughts to improve that experience would be to have the band, etc set back a little bit on the stage so there is better viewing from the balcony.  The second suggestion is to get rid of the first row, would make better for flow of traffic and visibility in the balcony.

We absolutely loved Imar and so grateful you brought them to this area.  We would love to attend more events with this style.
column18: I would also suggest providing posters in the Pendleton area for your events.  I just happened to see a poster while visiting in Starbucks in Walla Walla.  We are happy to travel from Pendleton for this quality of an event.

column17: Good music, quality musicians but it seemed repetitive and it all had the same intensity there was soft  Celtic music
Very fun and high energy band.
column18: Audience participation and enthusiasm is great. But when they holler, whistle and clap too loudly then it is difficult to hear the music. I wish they could respect the others in the audience more.

column18: Surprised access to the theater was restricted until a certain time so all patrons had to wait in the foyer. It seemed to be crowded and unnecessary.

column17: It was wonderful. The sound acoustics were great. The lighting was great. The group was worth it.
Very nice and intimate venu. Nice amenities and no complaints on the sound and lighting.
column18: It was hard to find the PDF tickets on the email. I suggest including Gesa Power House in the subject line of the ticket email so it’s easier to find in case you bought the tickets well in advance.
